            <title>[SPARK-30274] Avoid BytesToBytesMap lookup hang forever when holding keys reaching max capacity</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-30274</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;BytesToBytesMap.append allows to append keys until the number of keys reaches MAX_CAPACITY. But once the the pointer array in the map holds MAX_CAPACITY keys, next time call of lookup will hand forever.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
